Ad Text:
The Opportunity  
 
Join a highly reputable listed business and take ownership of end-to-end financial management for a major property asset portfolio. Partnering closely with the SLT you’ll play a key role in driving data-led investment and development decisions. You will be responsible for providing critical financial and strategic analysis to support property acquisitions, developments, and asset management decisions. This role will suit someone who enjoys diving into data, building detailed financial models, and influencing key business outcomes through strategic insights.

The Role 

Conduct detailed financial modelling, feasibility studies, and scenario analysis for new and existing property assets.
Evaluate development opportunities, acquisitions, and divestments, including preparing investment proposals and board papers.
Analyse market trends, rental performance, and portfolio returns to identify risks and opportunities.
Partner with internal stakeholders - development, finance, and operations - to ensure commercial alignment on major projects.
Prepare presentations and reports for senior management and external investors.
Drive continuous improvement in the use of analytical tools and reporting systems
About You

CA/CPA qualified
4–6 years’ experience in a property analytics role (preferably within commercial, industrial, or mixed-use sectors)
Advanced Excel and financial modelling skills
Strong commercial acumen with the ability to interpret data and communicate insights clearly.
Excellent stakeholder management and presentation skills.
What’s on offer

Premium package: $160k + super + bonus.
Hybrid/WFH (3 days on-site), supportive leader, promotion pathways and structured development.
Inclusive, collaborative culture with a track record of promoting from within.
Employee perks such as discounts on health care and insurance, salary sacfificing, additional leave benefits and an attractive bonus scheme.  
The Company 

Highly regarded and instantly recognisable, this listed organisation continues to deliver exceptional results. With a substantial property portfolio exceeding $2 billion, the business is investing heavily in ongoing asset development projects. Renowned for its market presence and commitment to developing its people, this is an outstanding opportunity to join a high-performing asset and property finance function that offers career progression, structured development programs, and exposure to complex commercial initiatives.

Apply Click Apply or contact Kavithri Weerasuriya on kweerasuriya@sharpandcarter.com.au

You’re only human.    

It’s a strange thing to say, because us humans are capable of incredible things. And at Medibank, we know our greatest potential lies in the people who work with us.    

We strive to make real, fundamental change, driven by a simple purpose: to create the best health and wellbeing for all of Australia.   

The Opportunity

Are you a strategic thinker with a passion for digital transformation? We are seeking a Senior Digital Business Analyst to join our Enterprise Delivery team within Customer Technology & Delivery. This role is pivotal in shaping customer-centric digital solutions that enhance experience, retention, and self-service across desktop and mobile platforms. 

You’ll work across the full delivery lifecycle, from feasibility to supporting testing and transition, while also helping uplift our Business Analysis Practice. If you thrive in a collaborative, fast-paced environment and are ready to make a real impact, we’d love to hear from you. 

*Please note that this is a 12-month Fixed Term Contract.  

Key Responsibilities: 

Lead the elicitation and documentation of business and system requirements across digital and enterprise initiatives.
Break down complex initiatives into epics, user stories, and customer journeys using tools like Jira and Confluence.
Facilitate workshops and ideation sessions with internal teams and external vendors to drive innovative solutions.
Ensure traceability of requirements through design, build, testing, and deployment.
Contribute to the continuous improvement of Medibank’s BA Practice, mentoring team members and sharing knowledge.
Support compliance with Medibank’s policies and regulatory obligations, while driving quality and operational excellence. 

Must haves: 

Minimum 5 years’ experience in business analysis, with a strong track record across Agile, Waterfall, and hybrid SDLCs.
Proven experience working on digital platforms and initiatives, with a clear understanding of customer-centric digital solutions.
Ability to engage stakeholders at all levels and translate complex requirements into actionable insights.
Expertise in process mapping and requirement documentation (including user stories).
Strong facilitation, communication, and stakeholder engagement skills.
A proactive, results-driven mindset with a passion for delivering business value through digital innovation. 

Imagine working with us… 

We understand that work means different things to everyone...  We know happy, healthy people make great teams, and great teams put more heart into each customer and patient interaction. And that’s why we’re reinventing work.     

Imagine a workplace where work didn't feel like work. 

A workplace where you could shape when and where you work to have more impact. 

Where flexible working isn’t a buzzword, it’s a reality.   

  

Imagine a workplace that helps you and your family thrive.  

Where connection, personal development and health and wellbeing are front of mind. 

  

For you, work should help you Live Better. It should bring you fulfillment and joy. And with Medibank, it could.  

Inclusion and Accessibility   

We believe in everyone's potential and strive to make Medibank inclusive for all, because different perspectives make us better. 

We encourage applications from everyone, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander candidates, those with disabilities, and LGBTQIA+ individuals. For any adjustments or alternative formats during the recruitment process, please contact us at careers@medibank.com.au.

Will you actively create a healthier future for tomorrow?

At Medibank we're encouraged to think big. We have a clear purpose to impact better health outcomes for our customers, patients and our community.

 

We celebrate diversity of thought because we want to make better decisions for our customers. As we work towards our goal of better health for better lives, we value the knowledge and contribution of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders. We are working hard to create an inclusive workplace and develop Indigenous careers.

Medibank has bold 2030 Vision to deliver the best health and wellbeing for Australia increasingly relies on succeeding in Digital. Digital platforms and engineering services will be a critical enabler for future health and insurance experiences we deliver to our customers. The current Digital platforms have strong capabilities but for us to win in the context of 2030 vision, our digital assets will need to be reimagined and further evolved that is scalable, increases agility and accelerate solution delivery with improved security posture. 

About the Role

We're seeking an experienced Data Solution Designer for an initial six-month contract engagement. This position is ideal for someone passionate about data, eager to learn, and capable of translating business requirements into practical, scalable solutions. The primary focus will be on data modelling and SQL, which is absolutely critical for success in this role.



You'll wear different hats—sometimes analysing data, sometimes designing models, and sometimes defining how solutions will work end-to-end. The right mindset, curiosity, and ability to learn are just as important as technical skills.



Key Responsibilities
Understand existing data solutions and design enhancements on top of them.
Develop end-to-end data solutions, including how data flows, where it's stored, and how it's presented.
Design data models using Kimball and Data Lake techniques.
Translate business requirements into clear technical specifications.
Investigate and analyse data to ensure accuracy and usability.
Document source-to-target data flows and perform data profiling.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to clarify requirements and communicate design decisions.
Work with cloud environments (AWS preferred) and modern data technologies.

What We're Looking For
Strong experience in data solution design or related roles.
Exceptional SQL skills (must-have), including advanced analytical functions.
Strong experience in data modelling and creating data marts.
Ability to analyse and interpret data effectively.
Exposure to cloud platforms (AWS ideal, others welcome).
Excellent communication skills to engage with business and technical teams.
Self-starter with strong initiative and investigative mindset.
Ability to wear multiple hats and adapt to changing priorities.

In this role, you'll be expected to quickly understand the existing solution and identify which hubs do what, then build on top of current designs while ensuring scalability and usability. Success will require strong problem-solving and analytical thinking—knowing where to start, what to do, and who to involve at each stage. If this sounds like you, we'd love to see your application come through!


A career with us


At Medibank, we believe work is something we do, not somewhere we go. Our modes of working - Collaboration, Connection and Concentration - help inform how your day is structured and where you choose to work will vary, depending on your role and requirements.  


The wellbeing of our employees is our priority. We encourage you to talk to us about any additional support you may require during the recruitment process, as well as how this role can be flexible for you. We encourage applications from candidates with a disability, if you require any adjustments or alternate formats of key information at any stage of the recruitment process, we welcome hearing from you.

Sydney / Hybrid

About BMD

BMD is Australia’s leading integrated engineering, construction and urban development business. As the largest privately owned civil contractor in Australia, BMD is at the forefront of excellence, with a growing international footprint extending to the Philippines and the United Kingdom.

Driven by a purpose of powering futures and creating enduring legacies, we deliver complex infrastructure solutions that connect and transform communities. For over 45 years, our diverse portfolio of projects and roles provides exceptional opportunities for our people to grow and make a lasting impact. As part of our team, you’ll help deliver challenging projects, supported by leadership within an inclusive people-first culture.

Benefits

We believe our people do their best work when they feel supported — personally and professionally. That’s why we offer benefits that go beyond the basics:

grow your career with specialised learning and development programs
be recognised at our annual employee awards event and through our Thrive reward and recognition platform
prioritise wellbeing with mental health support and discounted gym access
support your family with paid parental leave for primary and secondary carers and flexible work arrangements available
access perks with novated leasing, specialised Power Perks and discounts with hundreds of retailers.

Who we’re looking for:

Reporting to the General Manager - Corporate Finance, this newly created role offers the opportunity to shape the group’s FP&A and performance reporting function. You’ll help design forecasting models, streamline and automate reporting, and deliver insight-driven analysis that supports smarter, more informed decision-making across the business.

This role will suit a commercially minded FP&A Analyst looking for a step up into a more senior role, or a hands-on Senior FP&A Analyst who is eager to build a role and function from scratch. You will enjoy working with data, modelling, and business partnering to deliver insight and drive performance, and thrive in a dynamic, growing environment where you can shape processes and influence decision-making.

Using your high level of skills, you will be responsible for

Lead budgeting, forecasting, and planning processes across the group
Design and deliver performance reporting, dashboards, and KPI frameworks in Power BI and Excel
Updating and maintaining financial models (P&L, Balance Sheet and Cash Flow) and rolling forecasts
Ad-hoc analysis to support strategic business investments and initiatives
Financial management analysis of key group KPIs
Partner with business units to interpret performance, identify trends, and highlight risks and opportunities
Provide actionable insights and executive-level reporting for the CFO, CEO, and senior leaders
Collaborate with IT and data partners to enhance systems, data integrity, and automation
Drive continuous improvement in reporting, analysis, and performance management processes
Support scenario analysis, business cases, and investment evaluations

The successful candidate will lead by example with:

CA/CPA qualified or working towards qualification
3 to 6 years’ experience in FP&A, commercial finance, or similar analytical roles
Strong experience in budgeting, forecasting, and driver-based financial modelling
Advanced Excel and Power BI skillset
Excellent communication and presentation skills for senior stakeholders
Proven ability to translate financial data into clear, actionable business insights
Experience in multi-entity or high-growth environments preferred

Diversity and inclusion

We recognise that we are strengthened by diversity, and we embrace differences as an equal opportunity employer providing a flexible and inclusive workplace.

So, join our team, be yourself and help us power futures and create legacies.

We’re a purpose and values-led business guided by our values of family, empowered, collaborative and driven. For further details on what makes BMD unique, head to https://www.bmdgroup.global/careers

Due to the high volume of applications and enquiries, we are only able to respond to shortlisted candidates.

No agency submissions will be accepted.

Job Title: Emerging Technology Lead - AI, Data & Automation
Ad Text:
Emerging Technology Lead – AI, Data & Automation Lead innovation and shape the future of technology in a complex enterprise environment. This role drives the identification, testing, and scaling of emerging technologies — from ideation through to production — while building a small, high-impact team.

You’ll translate business needs into innovation opportunities, develop proof-of-concepts, build business cases, and guide successful pilots into production.

Key Responsibilities:

Ideate technology solutions to meet business challenges.
Lead proofs-of-concept and secure business case approval for rollout.
Use your data engineering or data architecture background to deliver scalable innovation.
Champion initiatives across AI, automation, and smart manufacturing — from Generative AI to driverless cranes.
Partner across business and technology to deliver measurable outcomes.
About You:
A strategic and hands-on innovator with experience taking ideas from concept to delivery. You thrive in ambiguity, love emerging tech, and can grow a small team into a powerful innovation engine.

Who we are

Jemena is an Australian energy company who own and operate more than $12.4 Billion worth of gas and electricity transportation assets across Australia supplying millions of households and businesses with these essential services every day.

We pride ourselves on our innovative approach, technical expertise, and dedication to safety, quality, and sustainability. Our Group’s over 3000 team members, consistently strive to make a difference in the communities we serve.

Overview of our role

Step into a role where your impact truly matters.

This exciting new opportunity will see you play a key role in supporting the goals of our Customer & Energy Solutions product line — helping keep our platforms and systems running safely, reliably, and with care. You’ll work in alignment with our business model, ensuring we continue to deliver on our service commitments and make a real difference for our customers.

As part of our Customer Solutions value stream team, you’ll help shape and nurture a modern technology stack built on SAP C4C and CDC, recently upgraded as part of our CX uplift transformation program. Together, these platforms bring to life a 360° view of our customers, helping us create simple, seamless experiences that evolve with their needs — and strengthen operational efficiency across Jemena’s Gas and Electricity distribution networks.

In this role, you’ll have the opportunity to collaborate closely with business stakeholders, applying agile ways of working to deliver meaningful outcomes where they matter most. You’ll also play an active part in our culture of continuous improvement — measuring progress, reducing cycle times, and finding smarter ways to work.

This is your chance to be part of a supportive, forward-thinking team where your ideas, insights, and energy will help shape the customer experience of the future. 

A little about you

3+ years’ experience shaping SAP Service & Sales Cloud (C4C) solutions.
Hands-on in designing, testing, and delivering customer-first SAP experiences.
Collaborate with teams and stakeholders to co-create impactful solutions.
Confident in user management and solving integration challenges.
Build trusted relationships and translate business needs into smart solutions.
Extend and enhance architecture with creative customisations.

Qualifications / certifications & Skills

Tertiary qualifications in Business or IT (or equivalent experience) valued.
Experience in the utilities industry highly regarded.
Confident ensuring solutions align with Jemena’s architecture principles.
Proven success in CRM project delivery and ongoing support.
Skilled in SAP C4C configurations, workflows, and customer service processes.
Familiar with integrations across ECC/S4HANA, CDC, and third-party platforms.

Why you should come and work for us 

Our people are our energy source and we offer meaningful benefits and rewards that work for you. We offer the opportunity for long term career growth as part of our talent development and succession planning process. Join our team and make a meaningful impact toward Australia’s “Net Zero” targets through the delivery of critical infrastructure projects and be a part of our journey to shape the future of the energy and utilities industry.

Jemena is among the first companies in Australia to be accredited as a Family Inclusive Workplace
flexible work arrangements, empowered to work your way & agile + additional leave benefits!
primary & secondary parental leave & well-being and family support benefits
numerous career development pathways + yearly financial support to upskill
annual bonuses + generous $$$ employee referral program
empowering you within a fun, diverse and inclusive culture
group benefits galore for all employees!
genuine focus on work / life balance

We are committed to developing a diverse and inclusive workforce that reflects the communities we are part of. We welcome applications from people of all ages, backgrounds, abilities, and identities. At Jemena, you belong.

Recruitment Process 

During our recruitment process, you will be required to undergo pre-employment checks including pre-employment medical, reference checks and a national police check. Notice to Third Parties: Jemena does not accept unsolicited resumes (or liability associated with fees or costs) from recruitment agencies, search firms or third parties. Interested candidates are welcome to submit their application independently.

The role

As our Manager Technology Assurance, you’ll be at the forefront of ensuring that Auto & General’s technology systems and digital platforms operate safely, securely, and effectively. You will lead independent assurance reviews across our technology landscape, assessing the effectiveness of IT controls, risk management practices, and emerging technology initiatives. Partnering with a team of Assurance Analysts, you’ll provide strategic insights that shape technology risk decisions, strengthen compliance, and support senior leadership in safeguarding the organisation’s digital environment. This is a pivotal role where your expertise will directly influence the resilience and reliability of our technology systems.


Position Accountabilities

In this role, you will:

Lead Technology Assurance Programs: Oversee and deliver the annual assurance plan with a focus on technology systems, digital platforms, and emerging technologies, ensuring IT controls are robust and effective.
Drive Regulatory & Policy Compliance: Ensure technology operations comply with internal policies and external regulations (APRA, ASIC), collaborating closely with the Compliance and IT teams to resolve issues.
Provide Strategic Technology Insights: Deliver actionable assurance reports and recommendations on technology risk and control effectiveness, influencing senior leadership and committee decisions.
Foster Stakeholder Collaboration: Build strong relationships with executives, technology leaders, and key stakeholders to embed a proactive technology risk culture.
Champion Innovation in Assurance: Continuously improve technology assurance methodologies, leveraging new tools and techniques to enhance efficiency, coverage, and insight.
Lead and Develop the Assurance Team: Mentor and guide Assurance Analysts in conducting technology-focused reviews, control testing, and risk assessments, ensuring high-quality outcomes.
Drive Strategic Tech Initiatives: Lead cross-functional projects related to operational and technology risk, providing assurance input for digital transformation, IT programs, and emerging technology adoption.

 

What experience you’ll bring

Proven Technology Risk Expertise: 5+ years in risk, assurance, audit, or compliance, including 2–3 years in 2LOD technology assurance or IT risk.
Technical & Regulatory Knowledge: Strong understanding of IT controls, risk frameworks (COSO, ISO 31000), and regulations (APRA CPS 220/230/234, ASIC RG 271).
Analytical & Strategic Thinking: Ability to translate complex technology risks into clear, actionable insights.
Qualifications: Bachelor’s in Technology, Finance, Business, Risk, or Law; professional certifications (CISA, CIA, CRISC, CPA) highly desirable.
Stakeholder & Communication Skills: Able to influence and present confidently to executive-level stakeholders.
Leadership Skills: Experience leading and developing high-performing assurance or risk teams.
Demonstrated expertise: in designing, executing, and overseeing complex risk assessments, control testing, and assurance reviews. 
Thorough understanding: of the Technology Landscape, especially emerging technologies with a risk lens.

 

Location –Toowong

Close to a variety of public transport and easy parking options, the Toowong office has excellent end of trip facilities (including secure bike storage and showers), outdoor spaces and plenty of modern collaborative areas to work and connect with colleagues. 

Conveniently based at Toowong Village tower with views of the mountains and the Brisbane River, our location is only 4 km from the city and provides access to retail, restaurants and other amenities.

 

The benefits of working at A&G

Be rewarded - we recognise high performance and reward our people for their hard work through bonuses and other perks.
Work flexibility - with options to work from home up to two days per week.
Options for leave - life happens, so we’ve got volunteer days, an additional paid ‘ME’ day, paid parental leave and the opportunity to purchase additional leave to cover all of the big stuff.
Grow with us - we’ve got learning and professional development opportunities to suit everyone.
Give back - our A&G Difference program gives you the power to change our community for the better through volunteering, fundraising and donation opportunities for causes that you’re passionate about.
Take care of yourself - your wellbeing is important to us and our healthy mind and body hub, mental-health support and fitness discounts will help you be your best self.
Celebrate the wins - we love sharing our successes and celebrating together - join us and you’ve got a ticket to our many on-site events throughout the year, family fun days and annual celebrations.
Save money - as well as discounts on insurance products, we’ve teamed up with some incredible retailers, hospitality providers and others to bring you discounts on your purchases, no matter where you are in Australia.

 

About us

Auto & General (A&G) is the fastest-growing major Motor and Home insurer in Australia, providing insurance products and solutions to safeguard a brighter future for our customers and community.  

Our range of general insurance products including Car, Motorcycle, Home, Contents Pet and Travel products are delivered through our multi-award-winning brand Budget Direct and partnerships with leading brands - ING, Qantas, Virgin Money and Coles Insurance.

We’re excited about the future and we’re always on the lookout for talented, passionate individuals who can help us achieve our goal of being Australia’s best insurer! If this sounds like you, apply today.

 

Auto & General values individual differences and believes in fostering an inclusive culture that creates a great place to work for all. 


*A note from Auto & General to recruitment agencies: We politely ask that you avoid making any approaches or sending any unsolicited resumes to our Recruitment Team or Hiring Leaders across our business. Auto & General is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

Federal Government Department – ICT Division
Location: Canberra, ACT (Hybrid – minimum 3 days in office per week)

Collaborate continuously with customers and internal teams — including developers, testers, and product managers — to refine requirements and deliver high-quality outcomes.

5+ years of relevant Business Analysis experience, with a focus on ICT procurement and requirement translation.
Experience working in iterative and incremental project lifecycles.
Ability to embrace change and adapt to shifting requirements.
Experience in Commonwealth or State Government environments.
Knowledge of ICT procurement frameworks and best practices.

The Institutional Banking and Markets (IB&M) business unit manages relationships with major corporate and government clients and institutional investors. The Global Economic & Markets Research (GEMR) division provides clients with regular, real-time research on the Australian economy, international economies (i.e. US, EU, China, Japan, UK and Canada), currency, fixed-income, commodities, and sustainability. The team provides exceptional research and insights, and their work primarily involves developing and communicating economic and financial market views.



What your day will look like:

As a director, you'll play a leading role in shaping and communicating strategic views on base and precious metals. Understanding the decarbonisation challenges facing the resources sector, particularly in Australia, will also be a subject that you will explore. You'll be a visible thought leader, delivering high-impact insights to internal stakeholders and external clients, and helping drive business outcomes across Institutional Banking and Markets.



Your responsibilities will include:

Monitoring, analysing, and forecasting base and precious metal prices
Producing original, timely, and thought-provoking research across written reports, presentations, videos, podcasts, and social media
Supporting trading and risk management activities with high-quality analysis and forecasts
Building strong relationships with key stakeholders and clients
Enhancing the brand and reputation of the team through media engagement and client interactions
Leading and mentoring junior economists, fostering a collaborative and high-performance culture
Adhering to editorial, media, privacy, and compliance protocols, including GEMR peer review procedures



What you'll bring

To thrive in this role, you'll ideally bring:

A deep understanding of commodity markets (preferably base and precious metal experience)
Contribute thought leadership to the decarbonisation of the resources sector
Relevant experience as a commodity analyst in finance, government, research, or related fields
Strong analytical capability and experience working with large datasets
Advanced technical skills in Excel and statistical software (R or Python)
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to distil complex ideas for diverse audiences
A collaborative and curious mindset, with a passion for learning and innovation
A bachelor's degree in economics (or equivalent); Honours or postgraduate studies highly regarded
A leadership style aligned with our principles: obsess over customers, lead as an owner, create exceptional teams, and be curious and humble



This opportunity will give you exposure to a wide range of stakeholders at all levels of the business whilst being part of a team that is focused, smart, hardworking, and passionate about our shared vision to create the very best experience for our customers.

As the successful applicant, you'll be rewarded with a structured career path within the IB&M business that offers a competitive market salary, annual performance incentives, and a flexible working environment.

Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you.

Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. We are working hard to build a team of people who represent the rich diversity of our customers and communities. If you're excited about this opportunity but you don't meet every single requirement, or your experience doesn't align perfectly, we still want to encourage you to apply. You may just be the perfect candidate for this opportunity or another within CommBank.

At CommBank we will inspire you with work that makes a difference, surround you with talented people that respect and value each other, and empower you to grow professionally and personally. Most of all, making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.

We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Global Technology Solutions (GTS) at ResMed is a division dedicated to creating innovative, scalable, and secure platforms and services for patients, providers, and people across ResMed. The primary goal of GTS is to accelerate well-being and growth by transforming the core, enabling patient, people, and partner outcomes, and building future-ready operations.

The strategy of GTS focuses on aligning goals and promoting collaboration across all organizational areas. This includes fostering shared ownership, developing flexible platforms that can easily scale to meet global demands, and implementing global standards for key processes to ensure efficiency and consistency.

What You’ll Do

We’re seeking a dynamic and experienced Lead Data Engineer to drive cutting-edge data solutions that will shape the future of healthcare technology. If you thrive in a fast-paced, innovative environment and have a passion for data engineering, cloud computing, and large-scale analytics, we want to hear from you!

Join our Global Data Platform - an ambitious, collaborative team dedicated to designing and delivering impactful data solutions across ResMed. We partner closely with business stakeholders to build high-quality analytics products that fuel data-driven decision-making.

As a Lead Engineer, you’ll be at the forefront of ResMed’s data strategy, leading the architecture and development of scalable data systems and business intelligence applications.

This role offers a hybrid working environment, with time split between our Bella Vista office and working from home.

What You Bring

Data Architecture: Lead design and development of core data architecture across platforms.
Real-Time Analytics & Streaming: Build solutions using Kafka and Flink to enable real-time decision-making.
Data Warehouse Development: Develop sophisticated data models using SQL and dbt on Snowflake.
Cloud Infrastructure: Implement Infrastructure-as-Code using Terraform to manage analytics platforms.
CI/CD & Automation: Drive automated deployment using GitHub Actions, manage repositories, and optimize workflows.
Leadership & Mentorship: Guide junior engineers, champion best practices, and shape data strategy.

Must-Have Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in a STEM field.
10+ years of experience with SQL on large-scale analytics platforms.
10+ years in software development (requirements, coding, testing).
6+ years of hands-on experience with Python, version control, and data pipelines.
5+ years managing GitHub repositories and deploying cloud infrastructure using Terraform.

Preferred Qualifications:

Experience with dbt, Dagster, and Snowflake.
Master’s degree in a STEM field.
12+ years of related experience in data engineering.

What We Offer:

Competitive Salary Package – Rewarding your talent and contributions.
Free Onsite Gym – Stay active and energized with convenient access to fitness facilities.
Employee Stock Purchase Program – Share in our success with discounted stock options.
Comprehensive Insurance Coverage – Including Life, Total & Permanent Disability (TPD), and Income Protection.
Collaborative culture – work with industry-leading experts in a supportive, fast-paced environment.
Career growth – thrive in a world-class tech ecosystem with global opportunities.

About the role

The primary role of the Director of Data and Analytics Engineering within the Global Data and Intelligence Platform (GDP) team is to lead the delivery of trusted, self-service analytics solutions enabling data-driven decisions across the corporate functions - Finance, Supply Chain, People, QARA etc., ensuring that we have the tools, capabilities, and insights needed to make data-driven decisions.

This role will be responsible for developing and implementing a strategic vision for data and analytics engineering, as well as for building and leading a high-performing team. This role will be a thought leader in AI to drive the application and adoption of emerging AI-powered data and analytics engineering tools, and for building a foundation of integrated data to enable AI-driven experiences across these functions. This role works closely with customers and other stakeholders to understand and define customer needs.

Let’s talk about responsibilities:

Implement data pipeline integrations and solutions, incorporating highly scalable cloud computing and large-scale data stores, including data lakes, data warehouses, and data marts.
Partner with business leaders to identify and address their data and analytics engineering needs, and data scientists/analysts to determine which data is needed for analysis and provide the required data and analytics engineering solutions.
Develop and implement a data governance framework to ensure the accuracy, consistency, and security of data
Focus on the development and implementation of strategic and operational objectives that help achieve the organizational mission. Implements organization strategies through the effective direction and management of employees and resources.
Regularly interacts with executives and/or major customers; maintaining relationships with key stakeholders at al levels in the organisation.
Interactions frequently involve special skills, such as negotiating with customers or management or attempting to influence senior-level leaders regarding matters of significance to the organization.
Provides leadership to managers, supervisors, and/or professional roles.
Collaborate with other data, analytics, and technology functions across the organization on analytics engineering solutions, share best practices and insights, and lead the adoption of enterprise analytics technologies


Let’s talk about Qualifications and Experience

Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Data Science, or related fields
Minimum of 12 years of experience in Data and Analytics Engineering, especially in Supply Chain or Finance domains. Experience in technologies like Snowflake, SQL, dbt, and Python is required.
Proven ability to work cross-functionally, develop analytics solutions to challenges, and drive the implementation of the solution
Ability to work well through ambiguity, confidence in making tough calls and leading through adversity with a sharp focus on the eventual right outcomes
Excellent communication skills with an ability to translate complex technical concepts into easy-to-understand stories and insights
Strong work ethic, commitment to sweat the details with extreme ownership and end-to-end thinking

Preferred:

Looks beyond existing methodologies and own discipline to define and resolve complex problems, has in-depth knowledge of organizational objectives.
Experience with AI and machine learning, with a record of practical application of these technologies

Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Job Description

KPMG Australia is part of a global network providing extensive services across a wide range of industries and sectors. Our people collaborate, share their expertise and create innovation as we partner with clients to solve complex challenges, empower change, drive, disruption and growth. We look for talented people with the potential to make an extraordinary difference for our clients, our firm and our communities.

Your Opportunity

KPMG’s Financial Risk Management (FRM) team provides specialist risk management services to a wide range of clients, spanning financial services, energy and corporate sectors. We have an exciting opportunity for a manager to join our growing energy and commodity risk service offering within FRM.

We help our clients with a large range of quantitative risk management services in the areas of energy and commodity trading functions.  As a Manager, you will:

Model Development and Validation – you will work with our clients to develop and implement a range of risk management models.  You will also perform independent model validation for a range of trading and risk management models implemented by our clients.

Derivative Valuation –assist clients to develop derivative valuation policies, methodologies, as well as a range of valuation models and tools.  We work both as independent advisors as well as specialists to KPMG’s external audit teams to perform a range of derivative valuations

Leverage your knowledge of Energy Trading Risk Management (ETRM) system vendors and system environments to provide our clients with advisory, benchmarking, implementation and post-implementation services.

Develop or review existing trading and risk management policies and governance frameworks. 

Trading Controls Assessment – Support our client’s internal audit functions, to ensure that control frameworks around our client’s trading operations are appropriately designed and operating effectively.

How are you extraordinary?

You are able to digest, distil, and communicate complex concepts in both written and verbal forms.

You are a strategic critical thinker, and love using that skill to solve complex problems and plan for the future.

You are able to quickly build strong relationships and network with a variety of stakeholders both internal and external.

Your Experience

We are looking for someone with experience working in energy and commodity trading risk management environments, and who has a keen interest in analytics and quantitative modelling, to join our growing team.  We want to speak to candidates with the following attributes:

Experience and understanding of energy markets, trading and risk (essential)

An interest in working on a diverse range of quantitative and qualitative modelling engagements across energy and commodity markets

Experience using statistical packages such as SAS, R and Python (not mandatory);

An ability to communicate and work with clients and team members, taking on mentoring and management opportunities as appropriate

An ability to build trust with our clients and develop a network of contacts within the market.

A demonstrated ability to solve new and technically challenging problems, either independently or as part of a small team

Strong interpersonal and presentation skills.

Additional Information

Our people are focused on creating a diverse and dynamic environment that embraces and values differences. We value the variety of unique experiences, qualities and characteristics our people possess and we share and learn from each other.

We are proud to be consistently recognised as an employer of choice for women, and for our achievements in LGBT+ workplace inclusion.

Our commitment to ‘Flexibility’ allows our people to manage the changing demands of work, personal or family life.

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Job Title: Manager, Data Analytics, Governance Risk & Controls
Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Job Description

Join our Governance, Risk and Controls (GRC) – Data Intelligence & Solutions team within the Consulting Division as a Manager based in Melbourne, where you'll support a wide range of high-profile internal audit and assurance engagements through the application of advanced data analytics. Working alongside a national network of professionals and partnering with some of Melbourne’s and Australia’s most prominent organisations, you’ll be part of a collaborative, positive, and purpose-driven team environment. This role is ideal for individuals with a background in data analytics, data science, internal audit, risk, or assurance, who are looking to expand their skill set into the risk data analytics and digital assurance space.

The Opportunity

Collaborate with internal audit and assurance teams to provide data analytics solutions that enhance the effectiveness of audit procedures and risk assessments.

Translate audit objectives into data-driven approaches, including data extraction, transformation, analysis, and visualization.

Deliver insights that support risk identification, process improvement, and control effectiveness.

Work with clients across various industries to solve complex business challenges using analytics tools and methodologies.

Contribute to the development of data analytics strategies and reusable solutions within the GRC function.

How are you Extraordinary?

You are confident using data analytics to synthesise qualitative and quantitative data from a range of sources to uncover impactful insights.

You are a kind and compassionate leader with a passion for continually growing your leadership skills to get the best out of a diverse and multidisciplinary team.

You enjoy working flexibly with great time management skills that allow you to manage multiple deliverables and produce work you are proud of.

You are a strategic critical thinker, and love using that skill to solve complex problems and plan for the future.

You are a teambuilder who does your best work with a diverse and multidisciplinary team around you to collaborate, share ideas, and learn together.

Your Experience

A passion for delivering innovative client solutions using your excellent communication and problem-solving skills 

A commercial and analytical mindset with well-developed written and verbal communication skills, and strong project management skills

Prior experience in internal audit, assurance, or risk advisory roles, ideally with exposure to data analytics.

Proven experience in data visualization using Tableau and/or Power BI

Familiarity with ETL and data analysis tools such as SQL, Alteryx, Python, R, or similar platforms (experience in one or more is desirable, but not essential).

Effective communication skills and the ability to work collaboratively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Qscan Group is a leading provider of diagnostic imaging services, committed to delivering high-quality patient care.

About the Opportunity

We are seeking a Senior Commercial Analyst to play a key role in delivering actionable insights and driving data-informed decision-making across the Qscan Group. Reporting to the Business Insights Manager, you’ll leverage your analytical expertise to interpret complex business data, uncover performance drivers, and support strategic and operational initiatives that enhance commercial outcomes.

The position is offered on a permanent full-time basis and is located at our Clayfield Support Office.

In this role, you will:
Deliver insightful analysis on business performance across the Qscan Group to support strategic decisions and operational optimisation.
Design, build, and maintain interactive Power BI dashboards and reports tailored to stakeholder needs.
Present regular reports to senior leaders, highlighting KPIs, trends, and actionable insights.
Partner with business leaders to analyse variances, explain performance drivers, and recommend corrective actions.
Provide analytical support for strategic planning, including scenario modelling, investment evaluation, and business cases.
Contribute to data governance initiatives, maintain a data dictionary, and drive improvements in reporting quality and timeliness.
Identify, quantify, and address data quality issues affecting analysis and reporting.
About You
We’re looking for a proactive, analytical professional who thrives in a fast-paced environment and enjoys turning complex data into meaningful business insights. You will bring:

A Bachelor’s degree in Business, Finance, Data Analytics, or a related field.
5+ years’ experience in commercial analysis, business intelligence, or financial analytics.
Advanced proficiency in Power BI, including DAX, Power Query, and data modelling.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a commercial mindset.
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills.
Desirable skills:

Experience with SQL, Python, or other data tools.
Familiarity with cloud data platforms (e.g. Azure).
Knowledge of data modelling techniques (e.g. Star Schema, Data Vault).
What you'll love:

You will be supported to participate in personal and professional development. 
A Flexible Work Arrangements policy to help you achieve the ideal balance between work and personal responsibilities.
A range of employee benefits, such as paid parental leave, annual flu vaccinations and Fitness Passport. 
Access to our Social Club – including events, giveaways and monthly raffles.
At Qscan Group, you’ll be part of a team committed to excellence, innovation, and compassionate care. Ready to make an impact? Apply now and help us shape the future of diagnostic imaging in Australia!

Qscan Group encompasses Qscan Radiology Clinics, South East Radiology, North Coast Radiology, Alpenglow Radiology, Envision Medical Imaging and ClinRad. Together, we offer comprehensive diagnostic medical imaging services across Australia, utilising advanced technology and subspecialty trained radiologists to ensure the highest standards of care. Each entity within our network contributes uniquely to our mission of excellence, providing consistent, caring, and professional services.

Location: Parramatta (Hybrid)
Rate: $80–$100 per hour + super
Contract: 7–12 months with potential to extend
Are you an experienced finance professional who thrives in complex, fast-paced environments? We’re partnering with a NSW Government agency seeking a Senior Finance Business Partner to deliver high-level financial and business advisory services across a large and diverse portfolio.
In this role, you’ll work closely with senior executives and operational leaders to provide expert advice on budgeting, forecasting, performance analysis, and strategic financial planning. You’ll play a key part in shaping financial decision-making and ensuring strong governance, compliance, and reporting outcomes.

Key responsibilities
Provide strategic financial analysis, reporting, and insights to support executive decision-making.
Lead budgeting and forecasting cycles for assigned divisions, including labour analytics, capital planning, and variance reporting.
Prepare monthly management reports and dashboards, identifying trends, risks, and mitigation strategies.
Support the preparation of business cases, funding proposals, and savings initiatives.
Collaborate across divisions to strengthen financial performance, accountability, and process efficiency.
About you
Strong experience in financial management, reporting, and business partnering, ideally gained in large complex organisations.
Skilled in interpreting financial data and communicating insights to senior non-financial stakeholders.
Excellent stakeholder engagement skills with the ability to manage competing priorities and deadlines.
CA/CPA qualification.
Commercial acumen and/or experience gained within a Big 4 or large professional services environment will be highly regarded.
Why apply?
Join a high-performing government team delivering meaningful outcomes for NSW.
Competitive hourly rate and flexible hybrid work arrangements.
Opportunity to contribute to financial transformation projects within a large and diverse agency.
For questions please reach out via email to jpriebee@quayappointments.com.au

Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
At Ambulance Victoria (AV) we are proud to share our commitment to save and improve lives by providing outstanding care for our patients. This is our promise to every patient, and it sits at the heart of everything we do. No matter what corporate or support role you play in delivering our critical services to Victorians, you will join a team dedicated to bringing our vision to be a world leading ambulance service to life. 

We are seeking a Senior HR Analyst to provide strategic analytical support to enable data-driven workforce decisions. This role leads the development of reliable reporting frameworks, dashboards, and predictive models that translate complex data into clear, actionable insights for senior stakeholders. 

This is a Full Time, Permanent position. While WFH/Hybrid options are available, it is essential that the successful applicant maintains a presence at Doncaster in line with our hybrid working model. 

About the role

Reporting to the Senior Manager People Systems & Insights, responsibilities of this position include, but not limited to:

Lead and develop business requirements through advanced analysis and expertise
Design and implement data collection processes, establish data governance practices, and develop data cleansing and transformation procedures
Actively promote and contribute to AV's information management program through data quality and reference data maintenance
Serve as a senior contact point for data analysis requirements and foster strong relationships with senior managers
Apply expertise in data modelling and visualisation to develop insightful reports and dashboards 

About you

To be considered for this position you will possess:

A postgraduate degree or relevant industry certification (or progress toward) with high level relevant experience, or an equivalent combination of training and sound experience within a data related discipline
Proven significant experience as a data analyst or business data analyst, with a strong track record of working with large and complex data sets.
Expertise in distilling complex analyses into clear, compelling narratives and visualizations tailored for senior management and non-technical audiences
Advanced proficiency in Power BI, demonstrated by the ability to design, develop, and deploy sophisticated dashboards and reports that drive actionable insights and strategic decision-making
Experience preparing and presenting high-level reporting diagrams using Microsoft Visio, with the ability to effectively communicate complex processes and data flows to stakeholders in a professional and easily understandable manner 

Please see the position description for a full list of position requirements and key selection criteria. 

Working at Ambulance Victoria

As a valued member of AV you will enjoy a professional working environment that recognises the importance of work/life balance. We offer salary packaging options, generous personal leave entitlements, accrued days off for full time roles, and other benefits including free on-site parking. 

We believe our people are our greatest resource and the sustainability of our workforce depends on how well we utilise our people's skills and abilities and whether our staffing reflects the diversity of the Victorian community.  If you are ready to be an integral part in bringing our values of Care, Accountability, Respect and Excellence to life at AV, we want to hear from you! 

Important information

By applying for a position, you agree to undertake an assessment of any Secondary Employment or outside interests, in line with AV's Secondary Employment procedure. This is required to ensure there is no perceived or actual conflict of interest for AV should you be successful and commence in the role. 

Successful applicants will need to be willing to complete pre-employment screening including references, misconduct and Police Checks. 

This position is classified AV5 under the Ambulance Victoria (Management and Administrative Staff) Enterprise Agreement 2021. 

The position description can be found on the AV Careers website https://careers.ambulance.vic.gov.au. 

How to apply

Your application is an integral part of the selection process and should include

Cover letter outlining your experience and interest in the position
Current resume

When submitting your application you will be required to address the following:

Proven significant experience as a data analyst or business data analyst, with a strong track record of working with large and complex data sets. Expertise in distilling complex analyses into clear, compelling narratives and visualizations tailored for senior management and non-technical audiences
Advanced proficiency in Power BI, demonstrated by the ability to design, develop, and deploy sophisticated dashboards and reports that drive actionable insights and strategic decision-making
Deep knowledge of logical and physical data modelling concepts (both relational and dimensional)

Please note: Responses are limited to 500 words each and a separate document responding to each the key selection criteria is not required. 

Applications must be submitted by 11.59pm AEDT on Wednesday 26 November 2025.  Applications must be submitted via the AV Careers Centre website https://careers.ambulance.vic.gov.au to be considered. Emailed applications will not be accepted. 

For further information, please refer to ‘Applying for a position with Ambulance Victoria‘. For any further queries please contact recruitment via recruitment@ambulance.vic.gov.au or 03 9840 3653.

 

At all levels of our organisation a diverse and inclusive workforce allows us to deliver the Best Care to the Victorian community, and helps create a healthier, more productive workplace for our people. In the event you require a reasonable adjustment to support your application for this role, please contact us at recruitment@ambulance.vic.gov.au and a member of our Recruitment & Selection team will be in touch.

Our customer is seeking the services of a Technical Business Analyst

**This role is offered as a 6mth fixed term salaried opportunity**

**Can be based in either Syd or Melbourne**

**This role sits between the Business Analysts and the Developers. The role is to take the stories / functional Specs and put them into technical requirements developers can work from. Possibly could be called a Systems Analyst**

The Technical Business Analyst plays a pivotal role in delivering comprehensive analysis across complex and strategic initiatives. Sitting at the intersection of business operations, delivery, and technology, the role is responsible for gathering, analysing, and documenting requirements; designing scalable, value-focused technical solutions; and ensuring their effective implementation across cross-functional teams.

This role translates business goals into actionable requirements, business rules, process models, data sets, and success metrics. It ensures that solution designs align with strategic priorities, stakeholder needs, and operational realities. The position also identifies opportunities to improve processes, enhance service delivery, and drive the adoption of digital and data-driven products and services.

Additionally, the Technical Business Analyst provides leadership within the analysis discipline—championing best practices, mentoring peers, and ensuring that analytical outputs consistently meet organisational standards for quality, compliance, and value.


SELECTION CRITERIA
Key requirements include:

Demonstrated ability to deliver detailed business and technical analysis for complex enterprise solutions, ensuring alignment with organisational strategy.
Proven experience with enterprise platforms such as Dynamics 365 (D365), Power Platform, D365CE, Microsoft CRM, D365FinOps, D365FO.
Proficiency in requirements elicitation, process modelling, user story creation, and defining clear acceptance criteria.
Solid understanding of data modelling, system integration concepts, and API documentation standards.
Strong stakeholder engagement and facilitation skills to drive consensus and support cross-functional collaboration.
Experience working within Agile, Hybrid, and Waterfall delivery methodologies, including use of tools such as Azure DevOps, Jira, and Confluence.
In-depth awareness of security, privacy, and compliance considerations relevant to solution delivery and enterprise architecture.
Demonstrated ability to collaborate effectively with external partners and manage diverse stakeholder expectations in complex environments.
Proven track record in enhancing organisational performance by delivering solutions that improve business process efficiency, reduce technical debt, and enable scalable digital capabilities.
Strong leadership and collaboration skills, capable of guiding cross-functional teams, mentoring technical staff, and fostering shared ownership of architectural outcomes.
Highly developed communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to influence senior stakeholders, facilitate governance forums, and translate complex technical concepts into clear business language.
Demonstrated analytical and problem-solving capabilities, adept at navigating ambiguity, evaluating solution options, and assessing risks across diverse technology environments.
Results-driven mindset, balancing innovation with delivery discipline to ensure solutions translate into measurable business value.
Sound understanding of security, privacy, compliance, and regulatory obligations, with the ability to embed these principles into solution designs and architectural decisions.
Proficiency in Microsoft Azure services and ecosystems (e.g., compute, storage, networking, identity, integration), applied within complex enterprise design contexts.
 
QUALIFICATIONS

Advanced business analysis skills, knowledgeable in BABOK and Agile BA frameworks.
Practical experience with process improvement methodologies (Lean, Six Sigma).
Experience in regulated sectors (e.g., financial services) advantageous.
Desirable Qualifications

Bachelor's or Master's degree in Business Analysis, Information Systems, or related field.
5+ years of relevant business or technical analysis experience.
Certifications such as CBAP or Agile BA are desirable.
 
KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES

Analysis & Requirements
Stakeholder Engagement & Facilitation
Solution Design & Implementation Support
Process Improvement & Data Enablement
Business Data & Insights
Knowledge Management & Collaboration

Challenger Limited is an ASX-listed investment management firm managing $123.9 billion in assets (as at 30 June 2025). Life with us is fast moving and always exciting. Together we’re driving to deliver our vision to provide our customers with financial security for a better retirement.

We achieve this goal by providing a work environment where people from diverse backgrounds, with a range of skills and experiences can contribute and succeed.

Join us as a Senior Financial Risk Manager  

An important role where you can drive strategic improvements and leave a lasting impact on our market and liquidity risk processes. 

Operating as a true financial risk partner and Market and Liquidity risk SME, you’ll work collaboratively with stakeholders across investment, credit risk, and actuarial teams on a range of projects and analyses. 

We work flexibly from our Sydney CBD Office where you can expect to work 3 days in the office and 2 days from home. 

We are open to considering applicants at both a Manager and Senior Manager level. 

About the role  

Our Financial Risk Team are a dedicated team of five professionals who oversee market and liquidity risk, the daily hedging process, and analyse exposures to various asset classes. The team collaborates with investment, credit, actuarial teams and management to manage financial risks and assists the CRO in defining financial risk appetite. 

As Senior Financial Risk Manager you’ll play a crucial role in identifying, assessing, and monitoring market and liquidity risks across our investment portfolios. You will work closely with senior management, portfolio managers, and other stakeholders to assess investment and risk management strategies that align with Challengers strategic objectives. 

Risk Modelling and Analysis: Conduct comprehensive risk analysis, implement modelling improvements, and ensure robust systems and processes. 

Risk Reporting and Monitoring: Prepare risk reporting and monitor portfolio risks. 

Business Partnering & Collaboration: You’ll collaborate and partner with portfolio managers and other key business stakeholders to evaluate new investment proposals and hedging strategies and provide meaningful risk insights and SME guidance. 

Stress Testing and Scenario Analysis: Participate in stress testing and scenario analysis to test our crisis management framework and ensure Challenger’s resilience. 

Projects and Continuous Improvement: Manage and refine risk processes, contribute to strategic projects across the Challenger Group and Challenger Life Company. 

Policy and Risk Committee Contributions: Prepare Risk Committee papers and policies, providing meaningful insights into financial risk. 

The skills you’ll need  

You’ll have demonstrably strong experience in the banking or asset management industry with a clear focus on market- and liquidity risk.   This will be coupled with a deep understanding of financial instruments, their valuation, hedging strategies, and risk modelling with a strong grasp of financial risk management concepts (market, credit, liquidity). 

You’ll need to have experience in identifying, assessing, evaluating, and managing market and liquidity risks with a track record of analysing complex problems and then developing and driving effective solutions. 

As well as; 

Proficiency in portfolio risk modelling and analytics, including Value-at-Risk, Expected Shortfall, stress testing, and liquidity ratios/projections. 

High-level user of Excel and other MS Office applications, intermediate SQL, Bloomberg, and risk management software. 

Relevant academic qualifications in a quantitative or financial discipline with a numerical or finance-related undergraduate degree. 

Post-graduate qualifications and certifications like GARP, PRM highly desirable 

Proven track record in investment management or trading would also be highly desirable. 

 
Additional Information 

At Challenger, we’re small enough to be agile, but big enough to accelerate bold ideas. We support your growth and development, offering flexibility and a culture that values your unique contributions. 

Competitive discretionary bonus scheme 

18 weeks paid parental leave for all new parents 

Challenger Day – one extra day off every year in recognition of the effort our people make.  

Additional support leave (fertility, gender affirmation) 

Extra superannuation contributions 

Employee share plan 

Employee Assistance Programme 

Subsidised on-site café and central location near Martin Place Metro 

Access to free onsite yoga, mindfulness and Pilates classes. 

Access to annual free flu shots.

Excellent communication skills, with experience presenting complex information clearly to diverse audiences.

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. The team 

Join ASIC's Strategic Intelligence (SI) team within the Registry & Intelligence group, where you'll produce actionable insights that shape organisational strategy and support confident participation in Australia's financial system. The team helps ASIC by providing economic and risk analysis, strategic data analysis and operational intelligence and leads ASIC's intelligence strategy. This role will contribute to the team's delivery of operational intelligence and implementing the Intelligence Strategy.

The role

As a Senior Analyst, you will:

Drive the development and implementation of ASIC's intelligence strategy and foster a strong intelligence culture.
Analyse diverse data sets to create clear, actionable insights and present findings in an engaging way.
Lead projects assessing strategic and emerging issues in regulated markets to inform ASIC's priorities.
Support people management within the SI team, promoting development and wellbeing.
Monitor regulated financial markets to identify key developments and risks to consumers and market integrity.
Collaborate with business, IT and analytics teams to design next-generation data-driven tools.
Work across ASIC on multi-disciplinary projects to deliver shared outcomes.
Strengthen the Registry & Intelligence group's influence and leadership across ASIC.

About you

In addition, you will have:

Postgraduate qualifications in a relevant field (e.g., intelligence analysis, finance, commerce) or equivalent senior-level experience.
Proven leadership in managing projects and mentoring teams within financial services, regulation, government or business.
Strong understanding of financial markets and regulatory implications.
Advanced qualitative and quantitative analysis skills, including data manipulation expertise.
Demonstrated project management capability with strong conceptual, analytical and resource allocation skills.
Excellent communication skills, with experience presenting complex information clearly to diverse audiences.

AEMO at the Heart of Energy 

AEMO is Australia’s independent energy system and market operator and system planner. AEMO’s purpose is to ensure safe, reliable and affordable energy today, and enable the energy transition for the benefit of all Australians.  Australian governments are now committed to a net zero economy for Australia by 2050 and our vision is to enable this. We have the once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to co-design the future of our energy systems, and our core values revolve around character, commitment, and connection. Join us as we contribute to this significant transition in the energy sector.    

About the role 

AEMO’s Corporate Strategy team shapes our organisational direction by developing a long-term vision, priorities and goals. We advise the Board, CEO and Executive Leadership on emerging strategic opportunities, challenges and trends, drawing on comprehensive energy industry analysis and organisational performance insights. Collaborating across all AEMO divisions, we provide a holistic, strategic perspective, enabling informed decision-making to best deliver on AEMO’s evolving role. The Strategy team also works closely across the organisation to translate our strategy into clear plans to deliver our vision and purpose. 

Reporting to the Group Manager Strategy, you will be working within a high-impact and tight-knit team, focused on analysing Australia’s energy systems and trends, assessing best practices from similar organisations, delivering insights to Board, Executive and Senior leadership, supporting the development of strategic priorities and guiding AEMO’s strategic planning process. Your contribution will be pivotal in shaping Australia’s energy future. 

What you will be doing 

In this role, you will leverage your strong foundations in energy industry and knowledge to analyse Australian energy system and market trends, undertake scenario planning and identify key implications to AEMO and the energy transition. 

Key accountabilities include:  

Undertake complex strategic analysis, developing and applying frameworks and tools.

Proactively monitor and evaluate local and international trends in the energy sector.

Develop actionable strategic insights and identify implications for AEMO, supporting the development and refinement of short to long-term strategic plans.

Track and prepare reports on the delivery of strategic initiatives across the organisation.

Monitor the key strategic performance indicators that tracks our performance against our long-term strategy 

What you will bring to the role 

We seek a critical and strategic thinker with strong foundations in the energy sector and a background in consulting, corporate strategy, energy operations or energy policy, ready to drive corporate strategy at a national level. 

Tertiary qualifications in a relevant business discipline (Engineering, Science, Economics, Commerce).

Strong foundations in a strategy-focused role, ideally gained within a leading consulting firm, corporate strategy function or a relevant energy industry context.

Superior analytical and modelling skills, with the ability to efficiency structure and undertake analysis with proficiency in using the tools available

Exceptional structured thinking and complex problem-solving skills, with an ability to strategically frame issues, and develop and rigorously test hypotheses

Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with experience working directly with senior management. 

In return some of our benefits to you 

Flexible working: work from home, part time, job share, hybrid options, and additional leave options

Professional development via projects, industry networks, job rotation, study assistance and more.

Give back with up to 4 days of volunteering leave per year.

Reward your hard work with annual performance bonuses (subject to eligibility).

Embrace a healthier you with our wellness program, discounted health insurance, gym perks and our comprehensive Employee Assistance Program (EAP).  

About Our Process 

At AEMO we are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workforce. We welcome people of all backgrounds, including people with disabilities and neurodivergence and those who identify as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander. If you have any accessibility requirements to support you during the application or interview process, simply let us know by emailing us at talent@aemo.com.au

Build and operate pricing models to meet business needs 

Broaden your career with one of largest General Insurer in Australia

Open to Sydney candidates only - Hybrid flexibility

About Hollard 

Hollard Insurance is part of the Hollard Group of Companies and a top 5 General Insurer in Australia and New Zealand. We underwrite a broad range of general insurance products, including motor, home, contents, business, bicycle and pet, in proud partnership with some of Australia's biggest consumer brands and broker businesses. As an independent and privately owned company, we believe we can go further together – for our people, customers, communities and partners – through an innovative approach to providing insurance. 

Our state-of-the-art facilities in North Sydney reflect our commitment to providing innovative workspaces that support hybrid and remote work. 

About the Role 

The Senior Pricing Analyst role supports the pricing of general insurance products using data analytics, statistical modelling, and in-depth knowledge of our products, customers, and partners to maintain a sustainable, profitable, growing business.

Key Responsibilities include (but not limited to):

Manage, interpret, and analyse internal and external data sources to establish prices for general insurance products.

Develop and maintain models utilising GLMs, machine learning, natural perils, geographic, and data science techniques.

Derive insights from models and analysis to recommend pricing and business actions to a variety of business units and stakeholders.

Implement pricing changes and quantify expected impacts on the portfolio.

Assist with management of customer complaints and remediation.

Assist with pricing team risk control management and reporting.

Provide analytical guidance and mentorship to junior analysts.

 About You 

4+ years of general insurance industry experience – pricing experience preferred.

Strong knowledge of the Australian general insurance industry and products.

Proven skills and experience with programming and data management languages such as SAS, SQL, Python, R

Proven skills in data visualisation tools such as Tableau or Power BI

Proven capability in developing advanced general insurance pricing, statistical, and data science models.

Demonstrated ability to explain technical concepts to a variety of audiences to enable effective understanding and decision making across the business.

Degree qualified in mathematics, actuarial studies, statistics, or similar quantitative disciplines.

Stakeholders' management expertise

 Working at Hollard 

At Hollard, you’ll discover an environment where you can truly make an impact. We offer the best of both worlds – the opportunity, agility and creativity of a company growing with scale, alongside a focus on becoming a catalyst for enduring, positive, social change. 

We’re a tight-knit team, where authentic voices and unique perspectives matter. We work supportively, collaboratively and inclusively to help shape our future and create shared value for our communities. 

Hollard proudly promotes flexible work including remote work, non-traditional work patterns, and work-family balance. We’re also unapologetically committed to creating a workplace that values your diversity with a true sense of inclusion.  We actively seek to hire for your different lived experiences, including as it relates to disability, ethnicity, faith, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, gender diversity, sexual orientation, age, neurodiversity. 

We’re building something special. Working closely with our industry partners to reshape insurance for the better, we’re people changing insurance.

We’re seeking an experienced Lead Data Engineer to drive delivery of a large-scale data migration and integration program within a major enterprise operating in the Financial-Services domain. The ideal candidate combines hands-on SQL and SSIS expertise with proven experience leading distributed delivery teams across onshore and offshore environments. This role will oversee the end-to-end migration of critical business and customer data as part of a platform transition initiative. You’ll coordinate activities across onshore and offshore teams, ensuring high-quality engineering outcomes while remaining technically hands-on in design, development, and testing. The position requires a mix of technical depth, leadership, and delivery discipline in a time-sensitive environment.

Key Responsibilities

Lead technical delivery for data migration and integration streams across onshore and offshore teams.

Design, build, and optimize ETL/ELT pipelines using SQL Server and SSIS.

Oversee development, testing, and deployment of stored procedures, data mappings, and transformation logic.

Provide technical guidance, mentoring, and code reviews to ensure quality and consistency.

Drive data validation, reconciliation, and performance tuning activities.

Partner with project management and testing functions to support dress rehearsals and production cutovers.

Maintain governance, documentation, and compliance with internal data standards and audit controls.

Skills & Experience

8+ years’ experience in data engineering, ETL, or data migration, with prior leadership responsibilities.

Expert knowledge of Microsoft SQL Server (T-SQL, stored procedures, indexing, and optimization).

Strong hands-on experience with SSIS for data migration, integration, and automation.

Proven track record delivering complex data migration or system consolidation projects in enterprise or financial-services environments.

Experience with data validation, reconciliation, and cutover readiness.

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills across technical and business teams.

Bonus: exposure to modern cloud or data-engineering tools (Azure Data Factory, dbt, Redshift, or Python).
